#Summary1=(human1) This poem tells of the strong childhood love of the narrator and the beautiful Annabel Lee many years ago in a kingdom by the sea, which led the envious angels of heaven to chill and kill her via a wind out of a cloud at night, though their souls cannot be dissevered and the narrator continues to dream of her and feel her bright eyes.

#Summary2=(claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022) In this poem, the speaker mourns his childhood love Annabel Lee, who was taken from him by jealous angels and death in a kingdom by the sea, yet their love endures beyond death as he lies beside her tomb, forever connected to her soul.

#Summary3=(gpt4o) In this poem, the narrator mourns the loss of his beloved Annabel Lee, a young maiden from a kingdom by the sea, whose love shared with him was so profound and envied by angels that it led to her untimely death, but he remains eternally connected to her soul, visiting her sepulchre by the sea as the moon and stars remind him of their enduring love.

#Summary4=(Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct; postedited) The poem tells the story of a romantic and eternal love between the narrator and Annabel Lee, who is taken away from him by her kinsman after she dies, but remains with him in his dreams and thoughts.

#Summary5=(Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct) In this darkly romantic poem, the narrator reminisces about his beloved Annabel Lee, lamenting her sudden death when she was young, and yearning for her even in her grave off the coast-language and imagery emphasizing their timeless, immortal love.
#Text=ANNABEL LEE .
#Text=IT was many and many a year ago , In a kingdom by the sea , That a maiden there lived whom you may know By the name of ANNABEL LEE ;
#Text=And this maiden she lived with no other thought Than to love and be loved by me .
#Text=I was a child and she was a child , In this kingdom by the sea :
#Text=But we loved with a love that was more than love —
#Text=I and my ANNABEL LEE ;
#Text=With a love that the winged seraphs of heaven Coveted her and me .
#Text=And this was the reason that , long ago , In this kingdom by the sea , A wind blew out of a cloud , chilling My beautiful ANNABEL LEE ;
#Text=So that her highborn kinsman came And bore her away from me , To shut her up in a sepulchre In this kingdom by the sea .
#Text=The angels , not half so happy in heaven , Went envying her and me —
#Text=Yes ! — that was the reason ( as all men know , In this kingdom by the sea ) That the wind came out of the cloud by night , Chilling and killing my ANNABEL LEE .
#Text=But our love it was stronger by far than the love Of those who were older than we —
#Text=Of many far wiser than we —
#Text=And neither the angels in heaven above , Nor the demons down under the sea , Can ever dissever my soul from the soul Of the beautiful ANNABEL LEE :
#Text=For the moon never beams , without bringing me dreams Of the beautiful ANNABEL LEE ;
#Text=And the stars never rise , but I feel the bright eyes Of the beautiful ANNABEL LEE ;
#Text=And so , all the night - tide , I lie down by the side Of my darling — my darling — my life and my bride , In the sepulchre there by the sea , In her tomb by the sounding sea .
